Abdomen. Completely black, with a light purple reflection and fine microtomentum distributed homogeneously. Syntergite 1+2 without lateral discal setae parallel to margin of syntergite; syntergite 1+2 and T3 with marginal lateral setae; T4 with basal setae; T5 with abundant, slender and long discal and basal setae. Terminalia: ST5 with oval lobes (
Fig. 5
); T6 short and separated from syntergosternite 7+8 (
Fig. 6
); apex of paraphallus with denticles; epiphallus long (
Figs 7–8
); epandrium subquadrate, with very long hairs; in lateral view, cercus straight and surstylus slightly sinuous (
Figs 9–10
); postgonite arched, pregonite with truncated apices, with three apical setae (
Fig. 11
).
